# Files excluded from the expo-updates runtime fingerprint (which decides
# whether an OTA update applies to an installed binary).
#
# eas.json: its EXPO_PUBLIC_* env values bake into the JS bundle at publish
# time and never affect the native runtime — but fingerprinting hashes it by
# default, so editing the Spotify client id there (2026-07-12 app swap)
# silently orphaned every subsequent OTA: new fingerprint, no matching
# binaries, updates published into the void. Build-relevant eas.json changes
# (node/image versions, profiles) affect BUILDS, which get their own
# fingerprint at build time anyway.
eas.json
